%N A033947 Smallest primitive root (in absolute value) of n-th prime.
%C A033947 If there is a tie (i.e., both +k and -k are primitive roots with the least absolute value), then a(n) = +k. - _Robert Israel_, May 29 2026
%H A033947 Robert Israel, <a href="/A033947/b033947.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%p A033947 f:= proc(n) local p,t,k;
%p A033947   p:= ithprime(n);
%p A033947   t:= NumberTheory:-PrimitiveRoot(p);
%p A033947   for k from 1 to t-1 do if NumberTheory:-MultiplicativeOrder(p-k,p) = p-1 then return -k fi od:
%p A033947   t
%p A033947 end proc:
%p A033947 map(f, [$1..100]); # _Robert Israel_, May 29 2026
